==Index methodology== Index providers differ in the ways they select and weight securities in the benchmarks’ return calculation. There are three key issues:<ref name="vanguard" /> #Security selection and weighting #Calculation of returns #Ongoing index maintenance
To make their indexes more easily investable for index funds, index providers have adopted [http://www.investopedia.com/terms/f/float.asp free-float] weighting, and added buffer zones to their methodologies. Free float weighting eliminates non-trading shares in a company's capital base. These can include cross-ownership of shares by other companies, government owned shares, privately held shares, and other restricted shares. A company's free-float weighting will reflect the actual amount of shares available for public investment.
All equity-index providers periodically adjust membership to reflect market changes as well as those made necessary by corporate actions such as mergers or spin-offs.<ref name="vanguard" /> Buffer zones reduce the amount of turnover incurred as stocks migrate across market capitalization and style boundaries. Lower turnover helps reduce transaction costs for funds tracking an index.
Each major index provider has a different methodology for determining buffer zones. For example: *CRSP: [http://www.crsp.chicagobooth.edu/indexes-pages/methodology CRSP U.S. Equity Indexes Methodology Guide]{{broken link}} *Dow Jones: [http://www.djindexes.com/mdsidx/downloads/meth_info/Dow_Jones_US_Total_Stock_Market_Indexes_Size-Segment_and_Style_Indexes_Methodology.pdf Dow Jones Size Segment and Style Indexes Methodology]{{broken link}} *FTSE: [http://www.ftse.com/products/downloads/FTSE_UK_Index_Series.pdf?836 FTSE UK Index Series, Ground rules] *MSCI: [https://www.msci.com/eqb/methodology/meth_docs/MSCI_Nov11_USMethod.pdf MSCI US Equity Indices Methodology (Nov 11)] *Russell: [http://www.ftse.com/products/downloads/Russell-US-indexes.pdf?272 Russell US Indexes Construction and Methodology] *Wilshire: [https://www.wilshire.com/indexinfo/pdf/Wilshire%20US%20Large-Cap/Wilshire%20US%20Style%20Indexes%20Introduction.pdf Wilshire U.S. Style Indexes: A Methodology Overview]{{broken link}}
The table below shows a summary of methodologies.
